-- ft.page: `inbox` and it's Usage

`-- inbox` can be used as part of blog posts.





-- pd.package: `inbox` and it's Usage
name: fifthtry.github.io/bling/inbox

`inbox` is a new conversation experince via using `FTD` lang:

To use `inbox` on your web package, add below into `FPM.ftd` file:

-- cb.code:
lang: ftd

\-- fpm.dependency: fifthtry.github.io/bling
\-- fpm.auto-import: fifthtry.github.io/bling/inbox





-- tf.markdown:

Once you add above lines into your web package, add `inbox` into your `.ftd` 
files:





-- cb.code: Example code for `-- inbox`
lang: ftd

\-- inbox.inbox: This is your Title

Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor 
incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis 
nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut






